rComments: Great professor -- tells you what to expect and expects you to stick with it!

Professor Ragheb is amazing. He is very inspirational about teaching Arabic. He explains the concepts clearly, and his classes are fun and enjoyable. He is always ready to help if you ask him any question. I had no background in Arabic, and I learned a lot. He is an amazing teacher. It was my favorite class.
One of the best professors I have seen at UofT! Attendance/participation is mandatory.

Amazing professor, knowledgeable and enthusiastic about teaching Arabic. It was one of my favourite classes at UofT. I am continuing with my Arabic language studies in large part due to Professor Ragheb!

Nice but kind of strict on students like a high school teacher. wants no phone, and rudely reprimands others in class if late or mistaken. Devoid of patience and can't stand been asked twice- he will look at you hard as if he sees something within you. He doesn't a praisable character but nice in content delivery.
Loves talking about Medieval Islamic History
Took the course as a semi-requirement, ended up loving it because of the prof!

Excellent prof!! Fantastic communication skills and very knowledgeable;  Although I had no previous background in the topic, I found the course really enjoyable and rewarding. Recommend and would definitely take other courses with this professor.
Excellent TA and a  great lecturer! Makes difficult material clear and engaging. Highly recommend!!
